<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="46">Introduction</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="46">
Sisorid catfishes of the subfamily Glyptosterninae are widely distributed throughout the highlands of southern Asia. Among them, members of the genus 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:0A1502AF-3B84-4BA1-95C1-C24D72CCC5EE" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sisoridae" genus="Pseudecheneis" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudecheneis Blyth 1860:154" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="46" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pseudecheneis Blyth, 1860</taxonomicName>
are easily diagnosed in having a thoracic adhesive apparatus consisting of a series of transverse ridges (laminae) separated by grooves (sulcae) (de Pinna, 1996; Roberts, 1998). 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:0A1502AF-3B84-4BA1-95C1-C24D72CCC5EE" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sisoridae" genus="Pseudecheneis" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudecheneis Blyth 1860:154" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="46" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pseudecheneis</taxonomicName>
species are found in the headwaters of major river drainages throughout the subhimalayan region eastwards to the Ailao Shan range along the upper Red River drainage and the Annam Cordillera. A previous study by Ng &amp; Edds (2005) recognized seven valid species of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:0A1502AF-3B84-4BA1-95C1-C24D72CCC5EE" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sisoridae" genus="Pseudecheneis" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudecheneis Blyth 1860:154" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="46" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pseudecheneis</taxonomicName>
, viz. 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Sisoridae" genus="Pseudecheneis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="46" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sulcata">P. sulcata (Mâ€™ Clelland, 1842)</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:31513E00-E57B-4618-A71C-41681FF7E329" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sisoridae" genus="Pseudecheneis" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudecheneis paviei Vaillant 1892:126 [2]" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="46" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="paviei">P. paviei Vaillant, 1904</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Sisoridae" genus="Pseudecheneis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="46" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="immaculata">P. immaculata Chu, 1982</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:CEBC96E6-EC0E-4B79-B0E1-C693E445CD64" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sisoridae" genus="Pseudecheneis" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudecheneis sulcatoides Zhou &amp; Chu 1992:111 [115]" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="46" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sulcatoides">P. sulcatoides Zhou &amp; Chu, 1992</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Sisoridae" genus="Pseudecheneis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="46" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sympelvica">P. sympelvica Roberts, 1998</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:C280D1E1-5F99-419A-94EC-8709045672E0" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sisoridae" genus="Pseudecheneis" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudecheneis crassicauda Ng &amp; Edds 2005" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="46" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="crassicauda">P. crassicauda Ng &amp; Edds, 2005</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:175A3E4F-DFFE-405A-A858-8920376B267D" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sisoridae" genus="Pseudecheneis" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudecheneis serracula Ng &amp; Edds 2005" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="46" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="serracula">P. serracula Ng &amp; Edds, 2005</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="46">
The identity of 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Sisoridae" genus="Pseudecheneis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="46" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sulcata">P. sulcata</taxonomicName>
has been problematic (Ng &amp; Edds, 2005), and the current status of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:DB70F0B4-4FB7-4148-A6B4-CC37F69F7DF1" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sisoridae" genus="Pseudecheneis" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudecheneis tchangi Hora 1937:348" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="46" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tchangi">P. tchangi (Hora, 1937)</taxonomicName>
is unclear. The study below is based on an examination of material identified as 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Sisoridae" genus="Pseudecheneis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="46" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sulcata">P. sulcata</taxonomicName>
from throughout southwestern China, India, and Nepal (including topotypic material of 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Sisoridae" genus="Pseudecheneis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="46" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sulcata">P. sulcata</taxonomicName>
) and clarifies the identity of 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Sisoridae" genus="Pseudecheneis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="46" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sulcata">P. sulcata</taxonomicName>
, which is redescribed below. Additionally, material from Nepal previously identified as 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Sisoridae" genus="Pseudecheneis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="46" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sulcata">P. sulcata</taxonomicName>
by Ng &amp; Edds (2005) is found to belong to an undescribed species; the description of this as 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Sisoridae" genus="Pseudecheneis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="46" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="eddsi">P. eddsi</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
, appears below. A second 
<taxonomicNameLabel rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
from southwestern China, 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Sisoridae" genus="Pseudecheneis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="46" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="stenura">P. stenura</taxonomicName>
, is also described.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
